# Edge Cases
Title: Edge Cases

## Dramatis Personae

ALICE - A character
ACT - A character whose name looks like a heading keyword
SCENE - Another confusingly named character

## ACT I

### SCENE 1

// Empty lines between elements


ALICE
Hello.


// Character name that could be confused with heading
@ACT
I have a confusing name.

@SCENE
So do I.

// Back-to-back page breaks
===

===

===

// Nested parentheses in stage directions
> The crowd (mostly tourists) begins to cheer.

ALICE
(looking around (nervously))
Is everyone here?

// Single character dialogue (one word)
ALICE
Yes.

// ALL-CAPS line immediately after a heading (no blank line separator).
// Under the strict cue rule, ALICE is NOT a cue — it becomes an implicit
// stage direction, as does the following line. Use a blank line (or `@ALICE`)
// to make this a real cue.
### SCENE 2
ALICE
No blank line before me.

// Very short scene
### SCENE 3

ALICE
Done.

// Trailing whitespace and empty final lines
ALICE
This line has text.
